RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXECUTIVE CHAIRMAN was squeezed at the start to trail down the backside, commenced his rally splitting runners at the quarter pole, swung outside in the four path with good run at the top of the lane and closed in strongly to collar the embattled leaders at the seventy yard pole, clearing off at the finish. ANARCHY prompted the pace three wide outside in the beginning, began to edge away for a clear lead at the three furlong pole, maintained a comfortable advantage turning for home, was asking for the wire just holding onto the lead inside at the sixteenth pole and faded in deep stretch just missing the save for the place share at the wire. EXECUTIVE SIGHT was situated on the rail having one rival beat down the backside, improved on the fence passing foes through the turn and finished up with intent on the fence to garner a minor share in the end. LAKE SHORE DRIVE was in the mix up front between the two leaders down the backside, could not match strides with the top pair at the three eighths marker and yielded to others in the final furlong. TOURIST'S DREAM watched the top three leaders outside down the backstretch, made little headway four wide outside horses on the turn and was not interested running down the stretch. WOOD BE WILD tracked the top three running inside foes down the back straight, made no impact around the oval and could not get involved in the stretch run to be a factor. HIGHLAND SOCIETY stalked near the rear outside rivals down the backstretch, could not keep up with horses through the turn and came up empty in the drive to the finish line.

GOOD SOLDIER stalked near the rear on the inside in the early going, advanced smartly running in hand on the rail at the half, burst between foes making a good move at the top of the lane and ran on determinedly on the fence, besting the rest at the finish line. GLENHOLME was in a good spot galloping along alone in third place down the backside, assumed command passing the tiring frontrunner midway on the final bend, was clinging to the lead at the furlong marker and fade late in deep stretch to be a clear third at the wire. BILL NEEDLE settled in mid-pack three wide outside runners down the backstretch, rallied smartly three wide around runners at the three eighths pole, chased the leader in the four path driving to the wire and ran on mildly to the finish holding on for a minor role in the end. SOCIAL JUSTICE was unhurried trailing down the backside, continued to see the field running around the far turn, swung out seven wide outside all rivals at the top of the stretch and finished up willingly down the lane. GROOM LAKE travelled in midfield between rivals down the backside, was urged with runners on each side at the three eighths pole, shifted out in the five path to be in the mix for a small piece of the prize straightening out for the drive but needed more late to be a presence at the wire. DAWSON SILVER stalked three deep outside foes at the half, kept pace with rivals three wide on the final bend, angled outside in the six path at the top of the lane and could not make any impact in the stretch drive. TWIXTER was content tracking the loose pacesetter down the backside, could not accelerate with pothers making a move at the three eighths marker and backed away turning for home. CHICAGO FREDDY caught a flyer leading this field into the first turn, opened up on the pack down the back straight, was collared outside midway on the far turn, offered no resistance and stopped on the fence in upper stretch.
